      <p>
        Discrete Mathematics is the field of mathematics studying discrete structures
        such as finite sets, graphs, and networks. These structures are particularly
        important in computer science. Because the objects are relatively easy to define,
        they also provide an excellent opportunity to develop mathematical proof-writing
        and logical reasoning.
      </p>

      <p>
        <i>From the FAU Catalog:</i> A proof-oriented approach to and applications of
        propositional logic, sets, functions, relations, combinatorics, graphs, and trees.
      </p>

